mongodb powered blogging system in python. no http frontend - only telnet :P
(c) Leon Szpilewski

server.py - simple sockets server
client_thread.py - thread handler, each connection gets one thread
blog.py - the blog itself. processes input, 'renders' blog

setup:
get mongodb running
get pymongo
create a db named 'blog'
create a collection 'admin' in db
add 'admin_pass' : 'yourpass' to the admin collection

how to post:
connect to port 1337 and enter the command 'post <yourpass>'. post away.

how to anything:
the command 'help' is there for you

dependencies: mongodb, pymongo, python 2.6

